Pre-tax losses at Oliver Resources, the Dublin-based oil and gas exploration
company, rose from IPounds 199,014 to IPounds 271,792 (Pounds 252,079), in
the six months to April 30 1991.
Revenue from oil and gas sales fell to IPounds 766 (IPounds 2,280), though
interest receivable and similar income doubled to IPounds 50,826 (IPounds
24,877). Losses per share emerged at 0.5p (0.3p).
